  "title": "Sie vs Du — Like Ningal vs Nee",
  "subtitle": "Module 1 · Lesson 3 · Part 2",
  "accentColor": "#d4a520",
  "scriptLines": [
    {
      "text": "Malayalam has Ningal and Nee. German has Sie and du. Use the safe one first.",
      "mood": "waving",
      "audioSrc": "audio/tts/v1-3-2/v1-3-2-line-0.mp3"
    },
    {
      "text": "Sie = formal (bosses, strangers, elders). Du = casual (friends, family, classmates).",
      "german": "Sie / du",
      "mood": "pointing",
      "audioSrc": "audio/tts/v1-3-2/v1-3-2-line-1.mp3"
    },
    {
      "text": "In doubt — Sie. Always safer. Never rude.",
      "mood": "thinking",
      "audioSrc": "audio/tts/v1-3-2/v1-3-2-line-2.mp3"
    },
    {
      "text": "Ask formally: Wie heißen Sie? — What is your name? Try it!",
      "german": "Wie heißen Sie?",
      "mood": "celebrating",
      "audioSrc": "audio/tts/v1-3-2/v1-3-2-line-3.mp3"
    }
  ],
